{
  "texts": [
    "For this reason, we treat the stellar sources with lower and higher activity levels separately, which are classified according to their I Hα index values.",
    "If the median of I Hα of multiple observations (denoted by I median Hα) of a stellar source is less than 0.5 (see Appendix A and Figure 14), it is classified as having a lower activity level; and a stellar source with I median Hα greater than 0.5 is classified as having a higher activity level.",
    "In order to recognize the objects with consistent Hα profiles in the line center from the class of stellar sources with lower activity levels, for each stellar source in this class, we calculate the correlation coefficients of the normalized fluxes in a 3 Å-wide linecenter band between the Hα spectrum with the smallest I Hα index value and other spectra with larger I Hα index value.",
    "The criterion for recognizing the consistent Hα profiles in the line center is that the minimum correlation coefficient of the normalized fluxes in the center band is greater than 0.986 (see Appendix C.2 for details on determining the criterion).",
    "The stellar sources in the lower activity level class that do not meet this criterion or have bad pixels in the line-center band of their Hα spectra are removed from our sample."
  ]
}